RCW 11.98B.150

Trust director—Rules applicable to trustees apply.

Unless the terms of a trust provide otherwise, the rules applicable to a trustee apply to a trust director regarding the following matters:(1) Acceptance;(2) Giving of bond to secure performance;(3) Reasonable compensation;(4) Resignation;(5) Removal; and(6) Vacancy and appointment of successor.

Unless the terms of a trust provide otherwise, the rules applicable to a trustee apply to a trust director regarding the following matters:

(1) Acceptance;

(2) Giving of bond to secure performance;

(3) Reasonable compensation;

(4) Resignation;

(5) Removal; and

(6) Vacancy and appointment of successor.

[ 2020 c 303 s 16.]
